. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Semisimple.html#Module.End.IsFinitelySemisimple","kind":"def","line":64,"name":"Module.End.IsFinitelySemisimple","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Semisimple.lean#L64-L67"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Semisimple.html#Module.End.IsSemisimple\"><span class=\"name\">Module</span>.<span class=\"name\">End</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsSemisimple</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/End.html#Module.End\">End</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A linear endomorphism of an `R`-module `M` is called *semisimple* if the induced `R[X]`-module\nstructure on `M` is semisimple. This is equivalent to saying that every `f`-invariant `R`-submodule\nof `M` has an `f`-invariant complement: see `Module.End.isSemisimple_iff`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Semisimple.html#Module.End.IsSemisimple","kind":"def","line":58,"name":"Module.End.IsSemisimple","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Semisimple.lean#L58-L61"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.Module.Torsion.Basic","Mathlib.FieldTheory.Perfect","Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.AnnihilatingPolynomial","Mathlib.RingTheory.Artinian.Instances","Mathlib.RingTheory.Ideal.Quotient.Nilpotent","Mathlib.RingTheory.SimpleModule.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Semisimple"}